container

Interface IContainerElement<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the typeparameter of the interface and the underlying element
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ContainerElement

    public interface IContainerElement<E>
    This interface specifies the behavior of a single element of a linked list that is managed by the Container. It takes a single typeparameter to determine the underlying type.
    Author:
    OOP

        Sets the next element that follows the current element. In essence the pointer to the next object is set.

      • hasNextElement

        boolean hasNextElement()
        Checks whether or not other elements are following the current one
        Returns:
